33:02.067 --> 33:05.026
- He's gonna make it.

33:05.070 --> 33:09.900
♪

33:09.944 --> 33:12.251
- We've done all we can.

33:12.294 --> 33:13.992
- He has to make it.

33:14.035 --> 33:16.124
- [whispering]
I know.

33:16.168 --> 33:23.175
♪

33:25.220 --> 33:28.223
Mark?

33:29.311 --> 33:32.314
- Mark?

33:32.358 --> 33:34.142
Mark?

33:40.105 --> 33:43.064
[hopeful music]

33:43.108 --> 33:49.897
♪

33:54.075 --> 33:55.337
- Blood vessels are degrading.

33:55.381 --> 33:58.514
- How much longer do you
give the patient?

33:58.558 --> 34:00.342
- Fifteen minutes, tops.

34:00.386 --> 34:02.692
- Dr. Reynolds, you're a go
on your lung transplant.

34:02.736 --> 34:04.216
- New donor?
- New antibiotic.

34:04.259 --> 34:06.609
We can treat the infected lungs
of the motorcyclist.

34:06.653 --> 34:08.437
- Now you can feel lucky.

34:08.481 --> 34:10.091
All right, everyone,
you heard Dr. Sharpe.

34:10.135 --> 34:12.354
Let's get to work.

34:12.398 --> 34:14.052
[indistinct chatter]

34:25.976 --> 34:29.371
- Dominic...

34:29.415 --> 34:31.373
would you come over here
and sit down with your wife?

34:31.417 --> 34:34.376
[somber music]

34:34.420 --> 34:40.469
♪

34:40.513 --> 34:42.993
Okay.
Thank you.

34:46.388 --> 34:48.390
[exhales heavily]

34:49.739 --> 34:51.959
Good.

34:57.138 --> 35:00.098
Can you two look at each other?

35:15.635 --> 35:19.595
Right now you're both in shock.

35:19.639 --> 35:24.296
You are both
in unimaginable pain.

35:26.776 --> 35:29.431
You are angry.

35:29.475 --> 35:33.131
You are lost.

35:33.174 --> 35:35.785
But that doesn't mean
that this is the end.

35:35.829 --> 35:37.265
♪

35:37.309 --> 35:39.572
It doesn't have to mean that.

35:42.662 --> 35:44.229
An event this traumatic

35:44.272 --> 35:46.361
can actually bring you
closer together.

35:48.711 --> 35:53.629
Because right now...

35:53.673 --> 35:56.806
you are the only one
who truly knows

35:56.850 --> 36:00.201
what the other one
is experiencing.

36:00.245 --> 36:03.161
You are the only one
who knows what the other one

36:03.204 --> 36:06.207
is going through,

36:06.251 --> 36:10.211
and what comes next
is going to be a challenge,

36:10.255 --> 36:12.387
absolutely.

36:13.867 --> 36:16.391
Things are not going to go
back to the way they were.

36:16.435 --> 36:19.307
They will never be the same,

36:19.351 --> 36:23.485
but don't you dare
turn on one another.

36:23.529 --> 36:25.835
["Shallows"
by Daughter playing]

36:25.879 --> 36:30.188
Instead, turn to each other.

36:30.231 --> 36:32.799
Lean on each other.

36:32.842 --> 36:35.323
You embrace
your grief together.

36:35.367 --> 36:37.107
♪

36:37.151 --> 36:40.154
And above all else, you talk.

36:40.198 --> 36:42.243
♪

36:42.287 --> 36:44.680
